get_coreurl[source]

get_coreurl(local:bool=True)

Set the core url for convenience

Type Default Details
local bool True If local uses local node, else uses Infura.io gateway
{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

How to add file to IPFS

{% raw %}

add[source]

add(a, b=<object object at 0x0000022D5E93D0E0>)

Same as operator.add, or returns partial if 1 arg

{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %}

This requires a local IPFS Node to be run. Set up your local node using info here.

Using local IPFS Node

Note: Full list of available params on add function can be found here

  1. Choose the core url using get_coreurl
  2. Call the add function with the coreurl and path
  3. Check the status of the response
  4. Status 200 indicates the request has been posted (check what other status codes mean here)
  5. You can check the file on either ipfs.io or infura.io
{% raw %} 
url = get_coreurl(); url

'http://127.0.0.1:5001/api/v0'
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
response, jsonobject = add(url, "../README.md")

Added ../README.md to IPFS -  Response 200
{% endraw %}

You can view the added file on ipfs.io

To view any CID on ipfs.io https://ipfs.io/ipfs/CID

{% raw %} 
jsonobject

{'Name': 'README.md',
 'Hash': 'QmXPhkw5QTpP4eqNVfAudVDj8waZYTBb4bToHApvRWwXB5',
 'Size': '1176'}
{% endraw %}

Using infura.io gateway

This works without a local IPFS node running

{% raw %} 
url = get_coreurl(local=False); url

'https://ipfs.infura.io:5001/api/v0'
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
response, jsonobject = add(url, "../README.md")

Added ../README.md to IPFS -  Response 200
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
jsonobject

{'Name': 'README.md',
 'Hash': 'QmXPhkw5QTpP4eqNVfAudVDj8waZYTBb4bToHApvRWwXB5',
 'Size': '1176'}
{% endraw %}

You can view the added file on infura.io

To view any CID on infura https://ipfs.infura.io/ipfs/CID

How to add a directory to IPFS

To add a directory, simply pass a directory as the filepath and set wrap_with_directory and recursive flag as true

{% raw %} 
response, jsonobject = add(url, "../test", wrap_with_directory='true', recursive='true')

Added ../test to IPFS -  Response 200

How to get a file from IPFS

{% raw %}

get[source]

get(coreurl:str, cid:str, output:str, **kwargs)

Download IPFS objects

Type Default Details
coreurl str No Content
cid str The path to the IPFS object(s) to be outputted
output str The path where the output should be stored
kwargs No Content
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

cat[source]

cat(coreurl:str, cid:str, offset:int, length:int)

Show IPFS object data

Type Default Details
coreurl str No Content
cid str The path to the IPFS object(s) to be outputted
offset int Byte offset to begin reading from
length int Maximum number of bytes to read
{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
response = get(url, cid='QmXPhkw5QTpP4eqNVfAudVDj8waZYTBb4bToHApvRWwXB5', output='test.txt')
{% endraw %} {% raw %}

get_peers[source]

get_peers(coreurl, verbose='true', streams='false', latency='false', direction='false')

List peers with open connections.

Type Default Details
coreurl No Content
verbose str true Display all extra information
streams str false Also list information about open streams for each peer
latency str false Also list information about latency to each peer
direction str false Also list information about the direction of connection
{% endraw %} {% raw %}
{% endraw %} {% raw %} 
response = get_peers(url)

get_dht_value(coreurl:str, key:str, verbose:str='true')
